  # 2. Create a **Zeit** account
  The **Zeit Now** platform is extremely powerful, but for now we can think of Zeit as a **dead-simple hosting service for our static website.** In the next few minutes we'll get deployment of our code to the web working with just one command in Terminal ðŸ˜² .
  >
  **First, visit [zeit.co](https://www.zeit.co/signup) and sign up**
  (choosing "continue with email" is fastest).

+img('../images/projects/dnd/zeit-signup.png', { screenshot: true })

:markdown-it
  When prompted, make sure to install the **Now CLI (Command Line Interface).** This allows us to write commands to deploy our website from Terminal, similar to `cd`, `echo`, and others from earlier.
  >
  To confirm that you're logged in and have Now CLI installed, return to your project directory in Terminal and run this command:

pre
  code(class='bash').
    <span class="hljs-built_in">now</span> --version

:markdown-it
  If all is well, that command should return the version number of your Now CLI.
